[[!meta title="Contribute"]]

Contributors are always welcome!

  1. [Get the source code](../get-memo) by downloading a release, cloning the
     repository or making a fork on [GitHub][gh].
  1. Hack.
  1. Check whether tests which were passing before you've begun to hack
     still do.
  1. Send your work to the Memo's author. There are several possibilities.
    * Use `git format-patch` and `git send-email`.
	* Publish your branch and ask me to pull from it.
	* GitHub offers a ['pull request'][1] feature.
	* Simply create a patch and send it to me.

[gh]: http://github.com/jstepien/memo
[1]: http://github.com/guides/pull-requests
